    "content": "\"For years, my son Ben lived in a world of his own. We visited parks and playgroups, but the noise and the 'typical' way of playing always seemed to build a wall between him and other children. Then we found Aaria’s Blue Elephant (ABE).\n\nAt their last event, something shifted. In a room specifically designed for kids like Ben, the sensory triggers were gone, replaced by understanding. For the first time, I watched Ben engage in what his therapists call a 'circle of communication' with another child over a simple sensory bin. It wasn't just a playdate; it was the first time Ben felt he belonged in a community. ABE didn't just give us an event; they gave us a breakthrough.\"",
