    "content": "Hi everyone. I wanted to share my experience with you all. It all started in 2024, when I was on Facebook and I saw a woman, Liji, share a post about free Art sessions for children with special needs. This was done at her home. She allowed me to bring my autistic son and my older son with adhd. I thought my older son wouldn't be allowed but Liji recognized adhd as a disability as well. She eased my concerns and was very welcoming. My boys enjoyed their time meeting the family and doing Art together. Fast forward to 2026, Liji announced an Easter even for special needs children. Lovely, I said to myself. The boys were so excited. I was not expecting this event to tug at my heartstrings.. as soon as I stepped out of my car, saw what an amazing turn out there was... All the parents with their children.. a community that lacks support for our special babies, was now here. Seeing Liji, her husband and her daughter - no words can really describe it. But you could feel love and inspiration. I am just so thankful to be part of something so special and to have my children be included. Truly, so very thankful. ",
